Description: Marlware pottery jar;with a low ring-base, bulbous body with shoulder; and a single handle at the base of the neck. Re-assembled from fragments; much of the body is missing.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.95, p.107, p.195, pl.37, p.219, pl.61)
